goals.question: What is the distribution of housing prices in the University District?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of housing prices in the University District and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the average rating of properties in the University District?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of ratings for properties in the University District and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the distance between properties and the University of Washington?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Housing Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of housing prices in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['bedrooms'], data['price'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of Bedrooms')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the number of bedrooms and the price of a property in the University District?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    property_counts = data['property_type'].value_counts()
    property_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', edgecolor='k')
    
    plt.title('What is the most common type of property in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Property Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Property Types'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['review_scores_rating'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average rating of properties in the University District?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Review Scores Rating')
    ax.axhline(data['review_scores_rating'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {data['review_scores_rating'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
